notes
PIs: K. Shiokawa (STEL, Nagoya Univ.) Y. Miyoshi (STEL, Nagoya Univ.),
     T. T. Tsuda (NIPR), and S. C. Buchert (IRF Uppsala)

We perform simultaneous observations of EISCAT and several optical
instruments (sodium lidar, FPI, high speed cameras, etc) for investigations on
(1) dynamical and chemical coupling of the polar mesosphere and D-region,
(2) effects of the geomagnetic activity on the thermospheric wind dynamics, and
(3) electron density variations of the ionosphere associated with
pulsating aurora.
CP-1 (CP-6) mode will be used for the UHF (VHF) radar.
We prefer good weather condition and some auroral activities for this
campaign.


